    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1927-01-04T03:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1927-01-04T03:00:00-05:00" n="808"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d808">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.05/84: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-01-04T16:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 4, 1927—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received January 4—10:17 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>5. American consul general at Shanghai reported January 3d that rendition of
                    Mixed Court was effected by exchange of notes dated December 31st<note n="31a"
                        xml:id="d808fn31a">For the English text of the exchange of notes on Dec. 31,
                        1926, see The Municipal Gazette (official organ of the Council for the
                        Foreign Settlement of Shanghai), vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">xx</hi>, No. 1064
                        (Feb. 18, 1927), p. 47; cf. The China Year Book, 1928, p. 468.</note> and
                    that first session of Provisional Court would be held January 4th.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
